    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. COLLINS of New York:H.J. Res. 96.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article V of the United States Constitution grants Congressthe authority, ``whenever both Houses shall deem itnecessary,'' to propose Amendments to the Constitution.____________________[Page H4276]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
